05:32.532 --> 05:33.965
Layla?

05:39.839 --> 05:42.501
Layla, are you okay?

05:49.248 --> 05:51.045
What's wrong, girl?

05:51.250 --> 05:53.445
Did you hurt yourself?

06:44.804 --> 06:46.863
And we're back.

06:47.073 --> 06:49.439
<i>You're listening to Headspace
on WZXB...</i>

06:49.642 --> 06:51.075
...Wolfbridge University radio.

06:51.277 --> 06:54.804
I'm Sarah Morris and as always,
I'm here with Dr. Roger Kane...

06:55.014 --> 06:57.448
...psychiatrist and head of
Wolfbridge's Psychology Department.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.909
And we've got Liam on the line.

07:01.120 --> 07:02.849
Liam, how can we help you?

07:03.055 --> 07:05.546
<i>Yeah, this is a question for Sarah.</i>

07:06.225 --> 07:07.351
Fire away, Liam.

07:07.560 --> 07:11.553
<i>I listen to your show every night.
You have a really sexy voice.</i>

07:11.764 --> 07:12.856
<i>Really.</i>

07:13.065 --> 07:14.657
What exactly is your question?

07:14.867 --> 07:18.564
<i>So, what do you say, Sarah?
Can I take you out sometime?</i>

07:19.338 --> 07:21.203
Sorry, Liam, my boyfriend
is understanding,

07:21.407 --> 07:23.272
but not that understanding.

07:23.476 --> 07:26.570
<i>So I guess a blowjob's completely out
of the question?</i>

07:28.481 --> 07:29.470
Not necessarily.

07:29.882 --> 07:32.112
Just bend down as far as you can,
open up wide...

07:32.318 --> 07:33.683
...and give it your best shot.

07:36.956 --> 07:39.254
Our next call is from Eric.
Eric, how are you tonight?

07:39.459 --> 07:40.983
<i>Okay, I guess.</i>

07:41.194 --> 07:43.025
<i>Actually, not so good.</i>

07:43.229 --> 07:45.197
<i>My girlfriend broke up
with me last week...</i>

07:45.398 --> 07:47.866
<i>...and I've been having a hard time
dealing with it.</i>

07:48.267 --> 07:50.167
Sounds like you really cared
about her.

07:50.369 --> 07:51.893
<i>Yeah, I still do.</i>

07:52.104 --> 07:53.537
<i>I think it was all my fault.</i>

07:53.940 --> 07:57.432
<i>Well, I'm a freshman
and I haven't made that many friends.</i>

07:57.643 --> 08:00.077
<i>I guess I just need
someone to talk to.</i>

08:00.279 --> 08:03.214
Well, that's why we're here, Eric.
Fire away.

08:17.964 --> 08:19.363
Hey, you still here?

08:19.565 --> 08:21.999
Hi. Just putting
the finishing touches...

08:22.201 --> 08:24.431
...on my ultimate breakup CD.

08:24.637 --> 08:26.468
You know,
one of the cry-in-your-beer...

08:26.672 --> 08:29.402
...women-are-nothing-but-cray
manipulative-bitches variety.

08:29.609 --> 08:30.769
For that last caller?

08:32.111 --> 08:34.135
I had Brandon get his info
before he hung up.

08:34.347 --> 08:37.009
- Sarah...
- I know. I just...

08:37.216 --> 08:38.547
He seemed so sad.

08:39.051 --> 08:42.077
You know, he was blaming himself
for everything he's going through...

08:42.621 --> 08:44.988
...and I knew what that feels like.

08:45.591 --> 08:46.853
I'm proud of you.

08:47.059 --> 08:48.754
What you've overcome
this past year...

08:49.495 --> 08:52.328
It's gonna make you
a great psychiatrist one day.

08:53.766 --> 08:54.926
I don't need to explain...

08:55.134 --> 08:58.160
...why a psychiatrist should never
hand-deliver a sappy mix CD...

08:58.371 --> 09:01.135
...to a broken-hearted
patient's bedroom, do I?

09:01.340 --> 09:04.400
It's a good thing
I'm not a psychiatrist yet.

09:04.610 --> 09:07.443
I'm serious.
Never underestimate the influence...

09:07.647 --> 09:09.672
...your words
and actions have on others.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.540
- Okay.
- See you.

09:12.752 --> 09:14.219
Bye.

09:31.304 --> 09:33.670
Thank you very much.

09:44.450 --> 09:47.942
This is more than a spoonful.
This is like a Mama Jug, huh, right?

09:48.154 --> 09:51.248
- Well, hello sweet cheeks.
- Don't touch my tits.

09:51.457 --> 09:53.425
That's the property
of Alpha Sigma Theta.

09:53.626 --> 09:55.150
Did you see that guy?

09:57.930 --> 10:01.593
I'm telling you, guys, I fucking aced
my poetry final this morning.

10:01.801 --> 10:03.564
- Poetry? Seriously?
- Yeah, man.

10:03.769 --> 10:06.567
My professor says
I'm the next rock poet in the making.

10:06.772 --> 10:08.967
My very own Jim Morrison.

10:09.175 --> 10:10.472
Who?

10:12.545 --> 10:14.274
What do you got there, Lukas?

10:14.480 --> 10:18.712
It looks like... I don't know.
Grilled shit on a bun?

10:20.853 --> 10:22.980
People actually get paid
to make this shit.

10:23.623 --> 10:27.389
- Should have went to culinary school.
- You're killing in bong hits and games.

10:27.593 --> 10:29.185
You might as well stick to that.

10:32.264 --> 10:34.425
Did you talk to your dad
about winter break yet?

10:35.067 --> 10:38.036
Yeah, I told him I was going home
with you and he's fine with it.

10:38.237 --> 10:41.172
Really? That is so awesome.
My family's gonna love you so much.

10:45.611 --> 10:47.238
So has anyone heard from Audrey?

10:48.581 --> 10:51.448
I left a message on her cell,
I just haven't heard back yet.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.710
Wow, the murders are all over
the news. It's...

10:53.919 --> 10:56.353
- I didn't realie her dad was a big deal.
- He's huge.

10:56.555 --> 10:59.524
He's been published
in every major Psych journal.

10:59.725 --> 11:02.023
Maybe I should try her cell again.

11:02.595 --> 11:05.928
Maybe you should give her some time.
She may not wanna talk about it yet.

11:07.266 --> 11:09.234
Yeah, I know.
I'm just worried about her.

11:11.604 --> 11:13.629
Jeremy, Jeremy,
little bit of vitamin C?

11:13.839 --> 11:15.773
That's my tiggity.

11:17.043 --> 11:18.635
I look so stupid without the one.

11:21.147 --> 11:23.274
All right, well, ta-ta.

11:23.482 --> 11:25.541
- Later, Ben.
- Did you see him?

11:35.728 --> 11:38.561
I'm never taking a shower again.

11:38.764 --> 11:40.732
- You showered in your bikini?
- Yeah.

11:40.933 --> 11:43.959
Some perv fraternity is making
their pledges install webcams...

11:44.170 --> 11:45.831
...in the girls' showers.

11:46.038 --> 11:47.335
- Yeah.
- Oh, come on.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.599
- I hear that story twice a semester.
- No.

11:49.809 --> 11:53.711
A girl in my theater class told me
that it happened to...

11:54.313 --> 11:57.077
It happened to, like, one of her friends
in another dorm.

11:57.283 --> 12:00.411
Hearsay. There's no way that
that's true.

12:00.619 --> 12:02.484
Well, I'm not taking any chances.

12:02.688 --> 12:05.316
I'm not ending up on the Internet
like last time.

12:17.369 --> 12:19.667
Your dad left another message.

12:20.773 --> 12:21.762
Yeah, I got it.

12:24.143 --> 12:26.611
He thinks you're coming home
for the holidays.

12:28.314 --> 12:31.442
I'll call him. Just as soon
as this term paper is out of the way.

12:31.650 --> 12:34.710
- How's it coming?
- Oh, so incredibly slow.

12:34.920 --> 12:37.388
- Yeah?
- Yeah, at this rate, I'll be up all night.

12:37.590 --> 12:38.887
Oh, okay.

12:39.091 --> 12:41.355
Well, in that case...

12:43.596 --> 12:46.861
...I am going to Jeremy's room.

12:47.366 --> 12:50.529
- I will see you in the morning.
- Oh, have some sex for me.

12:51.237 --> 12:53.797
Oh, you know I will. Oh, yeah.

12:54.006 --> 12:57.635
That's so unfair. Bye.

13:37.917 --> 13:39.578
Lindsay?

13:43.622 --> 13:45.385
Audrey?

13:47.326 --> 13:49.226
What's going on?

13:53.065 --> 13:55.431
Oh, my God, are you okay?

13:56.001 --> 13:57.491
Hey.

13:59.205 --> 14:00.604
He's trying to kill me.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.274
Who's trying to kill you?

14:06.345 --> 14:07.937
The Boogeyman.

14:09.081 --> 14:12.448
He killed my dad
and now he's trying to kill me too.

14:12.985 --> 14:16.250
I'm sorry, Sarah.
I didn't know where else to go.

14:16.455 --> 14:19.720
Audrey,
the Boogeyman didn't kill your dad.

14:20.159 --> 14:21.649
He did.

14:22.194 --> 14:23.957
I've seen him.

14:24.897 --> 14:27.058
He's everywhere.

14:27.566 --> 14:29.693
I thought I got away...

14:29.902 --> 14:31.392
...but he keeps following me.

14:31.604 --> 14:33.094
Sarah...

14:33.305 --> 14:35.205
...I don't wanna die.

14:36.642 --> 14:38.633
You're not gonna die.

14:39.745 --> 14:41.212
Come here.

14:46.585 --> 14:47.574
Hey...

14:50.222 --> 14:53.385
...I'm gonna help you through this,
I promise.

14:57.696 --> 15:00.324
You're gonna sleep here tonight,
okay?

15:08.374 --> 15:11.172
It doesn't matter where I sleep.

15:13.212 --> 15:15.271
He'll still find me.

16:00.926 --> 16:02.553
Where are you going?

16:06.165 --> 16:09.362
I'm just going to get some water,
okay?

16:09.568 --> 16:11.126
Lt'll just take a minute.

16:11.337 --> 16:13.032
Just try and go back to sleep.

16:13.238 --> 16:14.728
I'll be right back.

17:33.018 --> 17:34.781
Sarah?

17:47.366 --> 17:49.061
Sarah?

17:50.436 --> 17:52.267
Are you in here?

18:22.301 --> 18:25.930
Help! Somebody open the door!

18:26.672 --> 18:28.037
Open this door!

18:52.598 --> 18:54.589
Audrey, what's wrong?

18:56.101 --> 18:59.002
We have to go. Now.

18:59.204 --> 19:00.865
He's in here.

19:01.073 --> 19:05.066
Hey, hey, hey, it's okay.
There's nobody in here. Look.

19:07.946 --> 19:10.414
Look, everything is gonna be okay.

19:10.949 --> 19:12.439
Stop saying that, Sarah.

19:13.051 --> 19:14.541
Everything is not gonna be okay.

19:14.753 --> 19:16.015
Wait. Audrey.

19:19.958 --> 19:21.357
Audrey, wait. Audrey.

19:21.560 --> 19:22.549
He tried to get me.

19:22.761 --> 19:24.558
Audrey...

19:26.632 --> 19:28.293
Audrey, what happened?

19:28.500 --> 19:29.660
Nothing.

19:29.868 --> 19:31.699
Just go away.

19:32.404 --> 19:35.305
Oh, please open the door
and talk to me.

19:36.909 --> 19:38.604
Audrey?

20:03.735 --> 20:05.430
Ben. Hey, is David here?

20:05.637 --> 20:07.798
Hey, morning.

20:10.309 --> 20:13.176
- So you finally cut his tongue out?
- Yeah.

20:13.378 --> 20:16.040
Hell week. He can't talk to anyone
but his pledge brothers.

20:16.248 --> 20:20.878
Oh, so the Greek system
truly does provide community service.

20:23.021 --> 20:24.113
Bye.

20:28.427 --> 20:30.327
- You look stressed.
- Audrey's back.

20:31.196 --> 20:34.654
She thinks the Boogeyman
killed her dad.

20:35.467 --> 20:38.129
- What?
- She's convinced he wants to kill her.

20:38.337 --> 20:40.237
Will you check in on her
and make sure she's okay?

20:40.439 --> 20:43.306
- I've got finals and the radio show.
- Oh, yeah, no, of course.

20:43.508 --> 20:45.942
Thanks. I left a note for Lindsay.
Gotta go, I'm late.

20:46.144 --> 20:47.236
Well, hey...

20:47.446 --> 20:48.435
...are you okay?

20:49.214 --> 20:50.772
Fine.

20:51.383 --> 20:53.180
I promise.

21:04.663 --> 21:06.528
And we're ready for our next caller.

21:06.732 --> 21:09.724
Hi, you're on with Sarah
and Dr. Kane.

21:11.970 --> 21:13.562
Caller, do you have a question?

21:15.307 --> 21:16.797
Hi.

21:19.778 --> 21:21.643
I'm being stalked.

21:22.781 --> 21:25.511
<i>- It's Audrey.
- He won't leave me alone.</i>

21:25.717 --> 21:30.620
I don't know what else to do.
He just follows me everywhere I go.

21:30.822 --> 21:33.689
<i>Is he a friend, a boyfriend?</i>

21:35.227 --> 21:37.991
I'm afraid we need to know
about your situation fully...

21:38.196 --> 21:39.857
...in order to help you.

21:40.365 --> 21:42.492
<i>You wouldn't believe me
if I told you.</i>

21:43.168 --> 21:45.159
Why wouldn't we believe you?

21:46.238 --> 21:48.706
Because you don't believe
in the Boogeyman.

21:49.207 --> 21:51.607
What exactly do you mean
by the Boogeyman?

21:51.810 --> 21:53.903
<i>He killed my dad...</i>

21:55.180 --> 21:56.738
<i>...and those other people.</i>

22:00.018 --> 22:01.713
I'm next.

22:04.456 --> 22:08.017
Your father was one of those killed
at the Hillridge Clinic. I'm very sorry.

22:08.226 --> 22:10.285
You must be experiencing
a great deal of pain.

22:10.829 --> 22:14.128
Look, I know you don't believe me...

22:15.300 --> 22:16.597
...but you will.

22:18.270 --> 22:20.864
<i>Once I'm dead,
you'll know I was right.</i>

22:23.809 --> 22:26.676
Call campus security and get
someone over to Hammonds Hall.

22:26.878 --> 22:30.780
- Which room?
- 403. Her name is Audrey Allen.

22:30.982 --> 22:33.280
Tell them she may be suicidal.

22:34.252 --> 22:35.719
Sarah?

22:35.921 --> 22:37.445
Sarah?

22:39.524 --> 22:40.821
Hello?

22:42.694 --> 22:45.288
Let's begin
by clarifying a few things.

22:58.577 --> 23:00.135
<i>I understand your father
was killed...</i>

23:00.345 --> 23:02.939
...by a man
who thought he was the Boogeyman.

23:03.782 --> 23:06.910
No. No. Look, it was him.

23:07.119 --> 23:10.111
I've tried to tell Sarah
but she won't listen.

23:10.322 --> 23:13.018
I wouldn't believe me either
but it's the truth.

23:13.225 --> 23:15.420
He's real.

23:15.827 --> 23:17.192
I don't know what to do.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.296
<i>You do realize the Boogeyman
is a legend?</i>

23:19.498 --> 23:23.332
One that a very sick man used
as an excuse to hurt your father...

23:23.869 --> 23:25.769
<i>...but a legend nonetheless.</i>

23:26.705 --> 23:29.674
I found my dad's journal.

23:29.875 --> 23:32.139
Look, he knew
the Boogeyman was real.

23:32.511 --> 23:35.173
He knew he was gonna die.

23:35.380 --> 23:39.282
Look, my dad was trying to help
those people before they all...

24:15.153 --> 24:17.018
Hello, caller? Are you there?

24:25.297 --> 24:27.128
Caller, are you there?

24:27.799 --> 24:29.289
Hello?

24:32.204 --> 24:33.398
Yeah.

24:34.806 --> 24:35.830
I'm still here.

24:46.384 --> 24:47.976
Hello, caller? Are you there?

24:48.186 --> 24:49.175
Hello?

25:16.281 --> 25:18.374
- What's going on?
- Someone's attacking Audrey.

25:18.583 --> 25:20.517
- What?
- He's strangling her.

25:22.554 --> 25:24.715
Jesus Christ.

25:30.962 --> 25:34.090
Look, stay here. Stay here.
I'll call the police.

26:12.771 --> 26:14.830
You sure you're gonna be okay?

26:15.473 --> 26:18.033
All right, if we need anything else,
we'll call you.

26:30.488 --> 26:32.479
Did you tell them what you saw?

26:39.130 --> 26:41.894
Sarah, are you all right?
What happened?

26:43.134 --> 26:44.999
I heard someone say that Audrey...

26:47.539 --> 26:48.699
That she...

26:49.741 --> 26:51.606
It's not true, is it?

26:55.680 --> 26:57.079
She hung herself with a belt.

26:57.482 --> 26:58.744
Jee.

27:07.425 --> 27:09.825
I think I'm getting sick again.

27:13.865 --> 27:15.730
You feel fine to me.

27:17.936 --> 27:21.702
No, I mean sick.
Sick the way I was last year.

27:25.877 --> 27:28.710
I saw something in Audrey's room.

27:30.281 --> 27:32.806
Something that wasn't really there.

27:35.687 --> 27:37.416
What did you see?

27:41.393 --> 27:42.690
If you don't wanna talk about it...

27:42.894 --> 27:46.421
I saw someone standing over Audrey
like they had strangled her.

27:48.466 --> 27:50.058
Who was it?

27:51.770 --> 27:53.499
I don't know.

27:54.906 --> 27:56.999
Sarah, you were in shock.

27:57.676 --> 28:00.406
You witnessed one
of your best friends die tonight.

28:01.446 --> 28:04.415
- It's probably...
- It's the same way my mom died.

28:06.951 --> 28:08.543
What if it triggered something?

28:08.887 --> 28:11.913
Something that I thought
wasn't there anymore?

28:12.657 --> 28:13.988
No.

28:14.192 --> 28:16.057
Sarah, listen to me.

28:17.729 --> 28:20.027
After what you've been through
tonight...

28:21.332 --> 28:25.291
...you could tell me you saw
a herd of pink elephants...

28:25.570 --> 28:29.597
...in Audrey's room and I'd still think
you're the sanest girl I know.

29:33.037 --> 29:34.299
Hello?

29:35.607 --> 29:37.165
Hey.

29:37.408 --> 29:38.932
Katie...

29:39.244 --> 29:40.268
...hey.

29:40.478 --> 29:42.343
Sorry,
I'm a little jumpy this morning.

29:42.547 --> 29:43.775
I think we all are.

29:43.982 --> 29:46.416
They asked me
to pack up Audrey's things.

29:46.618 --> 29:50.281
- Already?
- Yeah, dorms close in 48 hours.

30:10.775 --> 30:13.209
You two were pretty close, huh?

30:14.445 --> 30:16.276
Yeah, we were.

30:18.783 --> 30:20.580
Hey, where should I send her stuff?

30:20.785 --> 30:23.618
The only contact listed was her dad.

30:27.192 --> 30:28.557
He was all she had left.

30:38.770 --> 30:42.672
Well, if there's anything of hers
that you'd like to keep...

30:43.641 --> 30:45.768
Yeah, I think there is.

30:55.119 --> 30:56.882
Thanks, Katie.

31:08.466 --> 31:09.490
He ain't here.

31:09.701 --> 31:10.929
- Where is he?
- Study group.

31:12.637 --> 31:16.437
Sarah, by the way,
I'm really sorry about your friend.

31:16.641 --> 31:19.269
A bunch of us were listening
to your show when she called in.

31:19.477 --> 31:20.739
It was pretty freaky shit.

31:21.846 --> 31:23.973
If there's anything I can do...

31:24.182 --> 31:26.980
- Thanks. Tell David I stopped by.
- Yeah, sure.

31:42.367 --> 31:44.835
I just can't stop thinking
about it, man.

31:45.036 --> 31:46.901
She said someone strangled her.

31:47.105 --> 31:50.268
Yeah, well, she was confused.

31:50.475 --> 31:52.739
I'm just saying it's fucking freaky.

31:52.944 --> 31:55.879
So am I helping you
pack your clothes...

31:56.080 --> 31:58.708
...or am I simply packing them?

32:02.954 --> 32:03.978
- Come in.
- Come in.

32:10.695 --> 32:13.858
Careful. I got high
just walking down the hallway.

32:14.065 --> 32:15.794
Everything okay?

32:16.067 --> 32:18.297
I found something in Audrey's room.

32:18.503 --> 32:19.800
Her dad's private journal.

32:20.872 --> 32:22.567
Audrey was right about her dad.

32:22.774 --> 32:24.867
He did believe
the Boogeyman was real.

32:25.076 --> 32:28.739
He thought he was some kind
of physical manifestation of our fears.

32:28.947 --> 32:31.142
Well, you said
he was a respected psychologist.

32:31.349 --> 32:33.579
He never told anyone
what he wrote in the journal.

32:33.785 --> 32:35.912
He was afraid
his patients would suffer for it.

32:36.120 --> 32:37.781
More like his career.

32:37.989 --> 32:40.651
His theory was that his patients
were susceptible to the Boogeyman...

32:40.858 --> 32:43.292
...because they believed in him.

32:43.661 --> 32:45.856
When you said
Audrey was strangled...

